<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1953-06-17T06:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1953-06-17T06:00:00-05:00" n="1184" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1184">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">641.74/6–1753: Telegram</note>
                            <head>No. 1184<lb/><hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in the United
                                    Kingdom (<persName corresp="#p_AWW1" type="from">Aldrich</persName>) to the <gloss type="to">Department of
                                        State</gloss></hi></head>
                            <opener>
                                <seg rendition="#left"><hi rend="smallcaps">top
                                        secret<lb/>priority</hi></seg>
                                <dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">London</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1953-06-17T12:00:00+01:00">June 17,
                                    1953—noon.</date></dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>6606. Eyes only Secretary. At meeting with <persName corresp="#p_CWS1">Churchill</persName> yesterday I told him I
                                felt President was concerned over tone of <persName corresp="#p_CWS1">Churchill</persName>’s message to President
                                concerning Egypt.<note n="1" xml:id="d1184fn1">Ambassador <persName corresp="#p_AWW1">Aldrich</persName> was in Washington when
                                    President <persName corresp="#p_EGAD1">Eisenhower</persName>
                                    received Prime Minister <persName corresp="#p_CWS1">Churchill</persName>’s letter of June 15.</note>
                                <persName corresp="#p_CWS1">Churchill</persName> obviously regretful
                                and said that he would “soften that up”. I did not understand this
                                to mean that he intended to alter his position but simply to express
                                himself less belligerently in future. He urged very strongly the
                                necessity of not disclosing in any manner to Egyptians the
                                development of new formula referred to in <gloss target="#t_Deptel1">Deptel</gloss> 7866, June 10. With this I am sure we all
                                agree.</p>
                            <closer><signed><persName corresp="#p_AWW1"><hi rend="strong"><hi rend="smallcaps">Aldrich</hi></hi></persName></signed></closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>